    public static final String CONST_HBAR_WHAT_IS_TITLE ="What is Hedera (HBAR)?";
    public static final String CONST_HBAR_WHAT_IS_CONTENT ="Hedera is a fully open source public distributed ledger that utilises the fast, fair, and secure hashgraph consensus. Their network services include Solidity-based smart contracts, as well as native tokenization, and consensus services used to build decentralised applications.";
    public static final String CONST_HBAR_MISSION_CONTENT ="Hedera’s mission is to become “the most decentralised public permissionless ledger in the market”, which they plan to achieve through a combination of “path to permissionless” network nodes and the “path to widespread coin distribution” HBAR cryptocurrency which keeps the network secure.";

    public static final String CONST_HBAR_USE_CASE_TITLE ="HBAR Use Cases";
    public static final String CONST_HBAR_USE_CASE_ITEM_TITLE1="Network Fuel";
    public static final String CONST_HBAR_USE_CASE_ITEM_TITLE2="Network Protection";
    public static final String CONST_HBAR_USE_CASE_ITEM_TITLE3="Travel";
    public static final String CONST_HBAR_USE_CASE_CONTENT1 ="Developers use HBARs to pay for network services, such as transferring HBARs, minting fungible and non-fungible tokens, calling smart contracts, and logging data. For every transaction submitted to the network, HBARs are used to pay fees that compensate validator nodes for bandwidth, compute, and storage.";
    public static final String CONST_HBAR_USE_CASE_CONTENT2 ="When HBARs are staked to network nodes, they have a weighted influence on consensus for validating transactions. Weighted voting makes it difficult and expensive for a bad actor to maliciously affect consensus — it would require a centralised authority to own and stake over one-third of the network’s total supply of HBAR.";
    public static final String CONST_HBAR_USE_CASE_CONTENT3 ="At Travala.com, we offer more than 3,000,000 travel products in over 230 countries available for purchase with HBAR. Plus, you’ll receive a 2% giveback in AVA, Travala.com’s native cryptocurrency, on every accommodation booking.  Travala.com’s intuitive booking experience is designed to be familiar and simple to navigate. Travellers simply choose their desired travel product(s), enter their details, and select from the variety of available payment options, including traditional credit and debit cards, BTC, and 90+ other cryptocurrencies.";

